{
  "texts": [
    "It is also important for research, where capturing longitudinal exposome data is essential for analysis of health outcomes.",
    "Housing stability is known to exist on a continuum, from complete stability (access to housing of reasonable quality in the absence of threats) to complete instability (no access to housing of reasonable quality) 6.",
    "It is well known that people who are experiencing housing instability (HI) are at greater risk for other health issues, including substance use, comorbidities, and mental illness 3, 7, 8.",
    "People facing HI are also at an increased risk for homelessness 5, 9, 10, which is associated with increased risk of morbidity and mortality 7.",
    "Patients experiencing homelessness are also more likely to end up in the emergency department, have longer hospital stays than low-income housed persons, and are less likely to use preventive services 3, 10."
  ]
}